author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: A young boy's determined refusal to attend school led to a comical scene as his family, opting for an unconventional approach, carried his entire bed to the school gates. The viral video shows the child clinging to his cot, much to the amusement of onlookers and social media users who reminisced about their own childhood school struggles.
title: Watch: Boy takes 'don't want to go to school' to new heights, gets carried on a cot

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Former opener Sadagoppan Ramesh slammed India's batting order flux in the second T20I against Australia. He questioned promoting Harshit Rana over Shivam Dube and Sanju Samson batting at number three. Ramesh stressed the need for clarity on player roles, arguing that inconsistent changes are hindering team performance and causing confusion.
title: 'A good driver can't become cook': Gambhir draws flak

author: SANJAY SHARMA
description: The Ministry of Education has announced that Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Computational Thinking (CT) will become mandatory subjects from Class 3 onwards starting in the 2026–27 session. The initiative, aligned with NEP 2020 and NCF SE 2023, aims to make AI a basic universal skill. With teacher training, ethical safeguards, and a focus on “AI for Public Good”, the curriculum seeks to prepare students for a rapidly evolving, AI-driven global economy.
title: CBSE rewires schooling: AI from Class 3; classrooms brace for disruption

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Lalu Prasad Yadav faces BJP's ire over Halloween celebrations, accused of hypocrisy after previously dismissing the Maha Kumbh as 'meaningless'. Videos of the RJD chief with grandchildren in costumes sparked criticism, with the BJP alleging an insult to faith ahead of Bihar polls. The controversy highlights political divides over religious and cultural observances.
title: 'Celebrating English festival Halloween': BJP reminds Lalu Yadav called Maha Kumbh 'faltu'

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Alejandro Juarez, a longtime New York resident and former Trump golf club worker, was wrongfully deported to Mexico after ICE agents placed him on the wrong flight. The error, uncovered through internal emails, triggered national outrage and a federal review. His lawyer, Anibal Romero, says DHS has admitted the mistake and is working to return him.
title: Former Trump golf club worker accidentally deported due to ICE error

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: US employers can now submit applications for crucial foreign worker visa programs like H-1B and PERM. The Department of Labor's Foreign Labor Application Gateway (FLAG) system is back online after a funding lapse caused a temporary shutdown. While processing has resumed, expect delays as the agency clears a backlog of applications.
title: H-1B visa LCA submissions: FLAG system back online; employers can resume applications

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India and South Africa are set to clash in the 2025 ICC Women’s Cricket World Cup final, with India aiming for their first title after two previous runner-up finishes. South Africa makes its maiden appearance in the final, having secured a dominant victory in their semi-final match.
title: History of Women’s World Cup finals: Which teams triumph and which missed out?

author: TOI Education
description: The US has implemented three major immigration changes affecting Indian professionals and Green Card holders. Automatic EAD extensions have ended, H-1B visa fees have risen to $100,000 for new petitions, and the civics test for naturalisation has become more challenging. These changes introduce delays, higher costs, and stricter eligibility requirements, directly impacting employment, career planning, and citizenship pathways for Indians. Companies sponsoring Indian talent are also adjusting hiring practices in response to the new rules.
title: US ends EAD extensions, hikes H-1B fees, toughens citizenship test for Indians

author: TNN
description: Lucknow Police have apprehended a six-member all-women gang specializing in gold ornament theft. The criminals employed a shocking tactic, feigning vomiting to create panic and distraction, allowing them to snatch jewelry from unsuspecting passengers. Recovered items include gold chains, a locket, and cash, with investigations ongoing for further connections.
title: Puke drama: Lucknow police bust all-women gang that used ‘fake vomit’ trick to steal gold

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Cricket legend Sachin Tendulkar lauded Rohan Bopanna's inspiring career as the Indian tennis star officially retired after over two decades. Bopanna, who achieved remarkable milestones including becoming the oldest Grand Slam winner and World No. 1, expressed his pride in representing India. He remains committed to developing the sport through his academy and UTR Tennis Pro.
title: Bopanna's retirement: Sachin Tendulkar - 'Always believed sport reveals character'

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Pune's Diana Pundole is set to make history as the first Indian woman to race a Ferrari internationally. Competing in the Ferrari Club Challenge Middle East from November 2025 to April 2026, she will drive the powerful 296 Challenge car across renowned F1 tracks in the region. This significant achievement aims to inspire more Indian women to embrace motorsport.
title: First Indian woman! 32-yo Pundole on the brink of history with Ferrari

title: 'Invaded roadshow, hurled abuses': Manoj Tiwari allegedly attacked by RJD ; files complaint with EC

author: TNN
description: Five individuals were injured, with two sustaining serious wounds, during Kannada Rajyotsava celebrations in Belagavi. Miscreants reportedly stabbed the victims indiscriminately near Laxmi Complex before fleeing. Authorities are investigating the incident, suspecting outsiders may be involved.
title: Knife attack in Karnataka: 5 stabbed during Kannada Rajyotsava celebrations; 2 critical

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: China launched its Shenzhou-21 mission, sending three astronauts, including its youngest ever, to the Tiangong space station. This marks the seventh crewed flight to the station, with the astronauts set to replace the current crew and conduct experiments with the first small mammals in orbit. The mission underscores China's expanding space program and its growing competition with the United States.
title: Mice on space crew: China launches youngest astronaut on Shenzhou-21 with 4 small mammals

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Saturday Night Live's New York City mayoral debate sketch featured Miles Teller as Andrew Cuomo, Ramy Youssef as Zohran Mamdani, and Kenan Thompson as Errol Louis. The chaotic debate took a turn with a surprise cameo from James Austin Johnson's Donald Trump, who declared himself the true star and potential next mayor.
title: SNL: 'Mamdani' steals the show, says 'hit me up at the ballot box, girl'

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A mass stabbing on a London-bound train left ten people hospitalized, nine critically injured, as a man armed with a large knife moved through carriages. Passengers fled in terror, with some describing scenes of chaos and blood. Police tasered and restrained a suspect at the emergency stop in Huntingdon.
title: ‘They’ve got a knife, run!’ Witnesses recount UK train stabbing horror; 9 critical

author: TOI Education
description: Uttar Pradesh MBBS seats: Uttar Pradesh has approved the addition of 950 MBBS and 271 PG seats across government and private medical colleges for the 2025-26 academic session. Government colleges will gain 200 MBBS and 233 PG seats, while private institutions will add 750 MBBS and 38 PG seats. This expansion increases total MBBS seats to 12,800 and total PG seats to 4,297, aiming to strengthen healthcare infrastructure, enhance medical education capacity, and address doctor shortages across urban and rural areas in the state.
title: Uttar Pradesh expands medical education: 950 MBBS seats; 271 PG seats added

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Varun Tej Konidela and Lavanya Tripathi celebrated their second wedding anniversary with heartfelt social media tributes and adorable family photos featuring their son, Vaayuv. Their journey, which began on the sets of 'Mister' in 2016, has blossomed into a beautiful family life. This milestone marks their first anniversary as parents, adding a new layer of joy to their union.
title: Varun Tej and Lavanya Tripathi mark 2nd anniversary, share pic withbabyVaayuv

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: US Central Command released drone footage showing suspected Hamas operatives looting an aid truck in southern Gaza. The operatives attacked the driver and stole the truck and its contents, undermining international efforts to deliver vital assistance. Senator Marco Rubio condemned the act, calling Hamas an impediment to aid for Gazan civilians.
title: Watch: Hamas loots Gaza aid truck; US military drone catches it on camera

author: TNN
description: A 25-year-old woman, Supriya, was discovered deceased in her locked Bengaluru residence on Saturday. Her body was found hanging in a room on the third floor. Police have seized her mobile phone for forensic analysis. A case of unnatural death has been registered following a complaint from her family.
title: Woman’s decomposed body found in rented Bengaluru house

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Legendary Kapil Dev lauded the Indian women's cricket team's exceptional performance, stating they are superior to his 1983 World Cup-winning squad. He urged fans to appreciate the team's intelligent and elevated style of play, not just the outcome of the upcoming World Cup final against South Africa. Dev believes the team is ready to create history.
title: Women's World Cup: 'Superior to us in 1983!' - Kapil Dev backs India to create history

author: AKHILESH SINGH
description: Bhojpuri folk songs are a significant force in Bihar's election fervor, with both NDA and Mahagathbandhan leveraging catchy tunes to attract voters. Prominent singers and actors like Manoj Tiwari, Pawan Singh, Dinesh Lal Yadav, and Ravi Kishan are amplifying campaign messages, while Khesari Lal Yadav leads the Mahagathbandhan's musical outreach.
title: Bhojpuri beats: Singers who rock the Bihar polls

author: MAHIYAR PATEL
description: Facing decades-long waits for employment-based Green Cards, many Indians are opting for the EB-5 investment program. This route, requiring significant capital, offers a faster path to US residency, especially for H-1B visa holders and high-net-worth families securing their children's future. Despite recent discussions of a 'Gold Card' alternative, the EB-5 program, bolstered by recent reforms, continues to see strong demand.

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Pakistani cricketer Sahibzada Farhan faced criticism for his reaction to fans chanting obscenities about Indian bowler Jasprit Bumrah.  The incident occurred during Pakistan's T20I series win against South Africa.  Farhan has a notable on-field rivalry with Bumrah.  The article also details Pakistan's victory in the final match.
title: ‘Bumrah ke…’: Pakistani fans cross line, Sahibzada caught laughing, clapping — video

author: PRIYANGI AGARWAL
description: Delhi's air quality has plunged into the 'very poor' category, with experts warning of a challenging fortnight ahead. Despite minimal stubble burning, local sources like vehicle emissions and construction dust are driving the pollution spike.  Respite is unlikely as the city braces for its most polluted period, with forecasts indicating continued poor air quality.
title: Delhi: November is here, brace yourself for most polluted fortnight; AQI back in ‘very poor’ zone

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: New documents reveal Jeffrey Epstein's financial ties to Wall Street figures, including Russian banks. JPMorgan Chase, which settled lawsuits for $290 million and $75 million, flagged over $1 billion in transactions linked to Epstein. Emails show discussions between Epstein and former JPMorgan executive Jes Staley about potential clients and meetings with Prince Andrew.

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: US and China have agreed to a temporary truce in their trade war, pausing new tariffs and export curbs. Key deals include China resuming significant soybean purchases, US cutting fentanyl-related tariffs, and China lifting rare-earth export restrictions. This de-escalation offers a year-long window for further negotiations.
title: US–China trade reset: From tariffs to rare earths — What Trump and Xi agreed on

author: BHANU PRATAP SINGH
description: A political murder in Bihar's Mokama has reignited fears of election violence after a local strongman, Dularchand Yadav, was killed during a poll campaign clash. His family blames JDU candidate Anant Singh, while Singh points fingers at rival Surajbhan Singh, whose wife is also contesting. The incident highlights deep-rooted caste rivalries and political complexities in the constituency.
title: Bihar polls: 20 yrs on, violence returns to Mokama as baahubalis clash for supremacy

author: TNN
description: A nine-year-old girl died after falling from the fourth floor of Neerja Modi School in Jaipur under suspicious circumstances. Police have filed a negligence case against the school management and staff, with CCTV footage recovered and FSL teams collecting samples. The school principal stated the girl asked for washroom access before the incident.
title: ‘Blood stains were washed’: Girl dies after falling from 4th floor of school

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Egypt has opened the Grand Egyptian Museum, a massive new archaeological museum.  It showcases over 100,000 artefacts spanning 7,000 years of history.  The museum's biggest attraction is the full display of Tutankhamun's treasures, reunited for the first time.  This grand opening aims to boost Egypt's tourism and cultural heritage.
title: Egypt opens $1.2B Grand Museum, showcasing Tutankhamun’s tomb in full for the first time

author: TNN
description: A stampede at a privately run temple in Srikakulam district, Andhra Pradesh, killed nine devotees and injured over 25 when a railing collapsed on a narrow staircase. Panic ensued in a crowd of over 20,000 gathered for Karthika Ekadashi, with poor crowd control and lack of official clearance contributing to the tragedy. Authorities are investigating the incident.
title: ‘Act of God, no one responsible’: Builder of Andhra temple where 9 died in stampede

author: TNN
description: A workplace dispute over switching off lights tragically escalated into murder in Bengaluru. A 41-year-old manager was bludgeoned to death with a dumbbell by a colleague after a heated argument. The accused, a 24-year-old technical executive, surrendered to the police. Investigations into the shocking incident are ongoing.
title: 'Bludgeoned to death with dumbbell': Techie kills manager in Bengaluru office; suspect surrenders

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: New Zealand's Kane Williamson has retired from T20 internationals to provide clarity for the team ahead of next year's T20 World Cup. The 35-year-old leaves as the second-highest T20I run-scorer for New Zealand, having guided them to the 2021 T20 World Cup final. He will now focus on Test cricket and spending more time with his family.
title: End of an era! Kane Williamson retires; calls for 'clarity’ ahead of T20 world cup

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India and South Africa's ICC Women's World Cup final faces a weather threat in Navi Mumbai, with rain potentially disrupting the highly anticipated clash. A reserve day is in place, and the ICC has outlined rules for reduced overs or shared trophies if play is impossible.

author: RAUNAK BOSE
description: The New York Yankees are reportedly targeting elite left-handed power hitter Kyle Tucker to bolster their lineup after a disappointing postseason.  With a potential massive deal, Tucker's blend of power, speed, and discipline makes him an ideal long-term cornerstone, potentially closing the door on Cody Bellinger and ushering in a new offensive era.

author: BARSHA DUTTA
description: Kayla Nicole's Halloween costume and song choice sparked outrage among Swifties, who interpreted it as a jab at Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce. Fans accused Nicole of jealousy and obsession, viewing her post as a deliberate provocation. This incident highlights how quickly fandoms punish perceived slights, even years after a breakup.

description: Google Cloud is experiencing rapid growth, fueled by AI demand and significant infrastructure investment.  Now a major revenue driver for Alphabet, it's challenging YouTube and closing the gap with competitors. author: LAKSHIMA SAREEN
description: Amazon's recent job cuts are sparking global unease. CEO Andy Jassy cited cultural fit, not finances, for the layoffs. This signals a shift where workers must adapt to AI-driven environments. Companies are hiring AI specialists while other roles diminish. Employees face uncertainty, with many seeking new skills to stay relevant in a rapidly changing job market.

author: TNN
description: A devastating stampede at a new Srikakulam temple claimed nine lives, including eight women and a boy, and injured over 25 during Karthika Ekadashi. A railing collapse on a crowded staircase triggered the panic. Authorities are investigating the lack of prior approval, poor crowd control, and inadequate security at the privately run shrine.

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Scientific astrologer Greenstone Lobo predicts a 90% chance for India to win the 2025 Women's World Cup against South Africa. He cites captain Harmanpreet Kaur's 'one-in-a-billion horoscope' and the team's 'Grey Lizards' as key factors. Despite South Africa's strong skipper Laura Wolvaardt, Lobo believes India's stars are aligned for a historic triumph.

author: AMIT KUMAR
description: India's women's cricket team, led by Harmanpreet Kaur, aims to secure their maiden World Cup title against South Africa on Sunday.  Following a semifinal triumph over Australia, the team seeks to overcome past final defeats. Former captain Anjum Chopra expresses confidence in Kaur's leadership and the team's ability to win, while also urging caution against a strong South African side.

author: ASHISH MEHTA
description: The Pushkar annual cattle fair witnessed a significant shift this year as Marwadi and Kathiawadi horse sales overshadowed traditional bovine trade. Horses and camels are increasingly being purchased for transportation purposes in rural areas, with bulls seeing a sharp decline in sales due to modern farming equipment. The highest horse sale recorded was Rs 4.

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: An early Saturday morning explosion at Harvard Medical School's Goldenson Building has been deemed 'intentional' by authorities. A police officer observed two masked individuals fleeing the scene just before the blast. While no injuries were reported, investigators are seeking public assistance to identify the suspects captured in released photos. The FBI is also involved in the ongoing investigation.

author: SAHIL MALHOTRA
description: India's ODI vice-captain Shreyas Iyer has been discharged from the hospital in Sydney after a week-long stay, including time in the ICU, following a fall during a match. He will remain in Sydney for follow-up care for the next seven to ten days, prioritising his complete well-being over an immediate return to cricket.

author: MAHIMA ROY
description: NBA star Dwight Howard's wife, Amy Luciani, has offered marriage advice to young women. This comes after she filed for divorce, calling their union 'irretrievably broken'. Luciani's recent social media posts suggest a potential reconciliation. She spoke about what successful men seek in a partner. The couple's marital status remains unconfirmed.

author: TNN
description: A woman in Ahmedabad filed a complaint against her ex-boyfriend for allegedly stabbing her husband near Jagatpur Bridge. The assailant reportedly entered the couple's car and attacked the husband with a knife. The husband sustained multiple stab wounds and received extensive stitches, while the woman suffered minor injuries.

author: TNN
description: Warrior Moms, a network of mothers advocating for clean air, has demanded an immediate public health advisory from the Union health ministry within 48 hours. The group seeks clear guidance on AQI and PM2.5 thresholds for children's safety, appropriate masks, and urgent paediatric care signs. They also urge enhanced pollution-related health screening by paediatricians and hospitals.
